I see the issue now. The problem is in the renderForm method where the checkbox labels include a "✓" character at the beginning. When these labels are saved and then rendered in the PDF, that checkmark is being interpreted as a special character.

Here's the fix - replace the chkLabel function in the renderForm method with this cleaned version:

Replace this:

```javascript
const chkLabel = (id, label, val) => `<label>${chk(id, val)} ${label}</label>`;
```

With this:

```javascript
const chkLabel = (id, label, val) => {
    // Remove the ✓ prefix and clean the label for storage
    const cleanLabel = label.replace(/^✓\s*/, '').trim();
    return `<label>${chk(id, val)} ${cleanLabel}</label>`;
};
```

And also update the collectForm method to store the checklist labels as clean text without the ✓ prefix. Replace the getChecklistData method with this:

