And when storing the checklist items, use the stored labels directly from a pre-defined clean list. The issue is that the checklist items are being saved with the "✓" character in them, and when generating the PDF, those characters are causing encoding issues.

The root cause is that in renderForm, the labels include "✓" as a visual indicator, but that same text gets saved to the database and then rendered in the PDF where it appears as garbled characters. By removing the "✓" from the stored labels and only using it as a visual status indicator in the PDF, the problem should be resolved.
